The two of them get mixed in with some pretty bad guys, but mid way through the deal David's best friend falls through, this leads to conflict between the two of them. David ends up returning to his old life and slips away with very small charges from the government.

text: This film ,despite its laugh-hard demeanour, was well organised and structured which allowed it to become a serious watch, rather than a humorous time filler for when you're waiting for your girlfriend to finish buying shit in the never ending John Lewis shopping centre of Leicester.   The reviews of various critics on board the IMDb website have been unfair regarding the overall rating of this film, however with a 7.1 it's not short of a decent approval. I believe the critics of this film expected more comedy and less seriousness.  Personally, I thoroughly enjoyed this movie and would describe it as a shorter version of the Wolf Of Wall Street, mixed with comedic action. The length of the film allows an ease of watching, opposed to the supposedly 'longwinded' Wolf Of Wall Street.  So get your mate ready, give your girl some dough, some peas, some green, some cheese (money, not real cheese), some 'don't spend too much' tokens and get your fat asses Into that cinema!
